## Part XIV — AI Applications Across the PE Lifecycle

### Fundraising and LP Targeting

AI systems analyze historical LP data, fund performance, and market intelligence to identify high-probability prospective LPs and optimize roadshow targeting.[web:16]  

LLMs assist with DDQ automation, offering document drafting, and LP Q&A chatbots, reducing manual work in investor relations.[web:21]  

### Deal Sourcing and Market Mapping

Graph AI and knowledge graphs link companies, executives, investors, patents, and sectors to surface non-obvious deal opportunities in specific themes.[web:7]  

Similarity search and clustering tools build dynamic market maps, highlighting adjacencies, roll-up opportunities, and white spaces for buy-and-build strategies.[web:5]  

### Due Diligence

AI parses and summarizes large volumes of contracts, financial data, and logs, flagging anomalies, risky clauses, and conflicting terms.[web:26]  

Models analyze customer sentiment, competitive positioning, market sizing, and cybersecurity signals, augmenting commercial and operational diligence.[web:23]  

### Portfolio Monitoring and Executive Dashboards

Integration with ERP, CRM, and data warehouses enables near real-time monitoring of KPIs, covenants, and cash flow projections.[web:7]  

AI-powered dashboards identify early warning signals, supply chain disruptions, and profitability issues, providing CFO copilots and board-ready insights.[web:21]  

### Valuation and Scenario Analysis

AI assists with selection of relevant trading and transaction comparables, scenario modeling, Monte Carlo simulations, and sensitivity analysis.[web:26]  

Macro and sector models feed probability-weighted valuations under different economic regimes, improving risk-adjusted decision-making.[web:23]  

### Risk Monitoring and Shock Propagation

Portfolio knowledge graphs map exposures across counterparties, geographies, sectors, and supply chains.[web:7]  

AI simulates propagation of events (currency shocks, geopolitical crises, regulatory changes) across portfolios, generating alerts and recommended mitigations.[web:21]  

### Exit Planning and Buyer Matching

Tools scan potential strategic and financial buyers, analyze historical deal behavior, and match portfolio assets to likely acquirers or IPO windows.[web:21]  

AI helps draft marketing materials, optimize timing, and price range recommendations based on market sentiment and comparable transactions.[web:26]  

