## Part XV — Future of Private Equity

### AI-Native PE Firms

AI-native PE firms will treat data pipelines, knowledge graphs, and continuous valuation engines as core infrastructure rather than add-ons.[web:18]  

They will operate with always-on diligence, autonomous portfolio monitoring, and self-updating investment memos and LP reporting systems.[web:19]  

### Continuous Valuation and Digital Twins

Each portfolio company may have a “digital twin”—a model capturing its financials, operations, and market context—which updates valuations and risk metrics automatically as new data arrives.[web:23]  

Scenario engines will run in the background, constantly stress-testing portfolios under macro, sector, and micro events, surfacing interventions when risk-reward profiles shift.[web:21]  

### Autonomous Monitoring and Reporting

Agentic systems will monitor covenants, performance KPIs, ESG metrics, and regulatory changes, generating proactive alerts and recommended actions for deal teams and operating partners.[web:18]  

LP reporting may evolve into interactive dashboards where investors can query fund data, scenario outcomes, and risk metrics via natural language in real time.[web:19]  

